The game Aiyawatstani is played by two players on a 5x5 rectangle board with square tiling. All players play with Counters. Rules for Pieces: Counters hop adjacent or step adjacent. Players take turns moving. Setup: Place a Counter for player one at the union of the vertexes with coordinates [C5, G5], each vertex of the 0 row, each vertex of the 1 row, each vertex of the 2 row and each vertex of the 3 row. Place a Counter for player two at the union of the vertexes with coordinates [A5, I5], each vertex of the 5 row, each vertex of the 6 row, each vertex of the 7 row and each vertex of the 8 row.. Rules: Move one of your pieces. Aim: If the next player cannot move, the next player loses. The Aiyawatstani (Ludii 1) ruleset.
